WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:05.451
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:00:07.112 --> 00:00:09.197
The collapse
of the Mapo Citizens' Apartment

00:00:09.281 --> 00:00:11.199
already notorious for shoddy construction…

00:00:11.283 --> 00:00:13.827
Would you look at that?
The world has gone crazy.

00:00:13.910 --> 00:00:15.954
It's not long
before everything goes to hell.

00:00:16.538 --> 00:00:18.248
Well, I guess it had a good run.

00:00:18.874 --> 00:00:22.085
One day, the whole world will come
crashing down like that apartment.

00:00:22.169 --> 00:00:24.421
Will you stop with the doom
and gloom already?

00:00:24.504 --> 00:00:27.716
What about our Huijeong?
Want her to die before she even blooms?

00:00:27.799 --> 00:00:30.969
I'm just saying. The world is
not going to fold that easily.

00:00:31.053 --> 00:00:32.346
The doenjang stew is good.

00:00:32.429 --> 00:00:34.264
I'm scared the baby might hear you.

00:00:35.098 --> 00:00:38.602
With its so-called dad
spouting that kind of talk,

00:00:38.685 --> 00:00:40.687
you think it'd even want to be born?

00:00:40.771 --> 00:00:43.106
Geez. I'm sorry, okay? Let's just eat.

00:00:48.153 --> 00:00:49.237
Who's that?

00:00:51.490 --> 00:00:53.241
Damn, who is it?

00:00:53.325 --> 00:00:55.410
Mr. Kim, it…
It's Robert.

00:01:00.999 --> 00:01:02.000
Are you nuts?

00:01:02.709 --> 00:01:04.461
I told you not to come to my house.

00:01:04.544 --> 00:01:07.547
Mr. Kim, we're going back
to the States next week.

00:01:07.631 --> 00:01:10.175
For old times' sake,
let me have it just this once.

00:01:10.258 --> 00:01:11.510
I'll pay you double.

00:01:12.886 --> 00:01:13.887
Double?

00:01:15.472 --> 00:01:16.515
Damn it.

00:01:18.225 --> 00:01:19.309
Come on.

00:01:22.938 --> 00:01:25.816
Have you lost it?
What were you thinking calling them here?

00:01:26.608 --> 00:01:29.111
I didn't. They showed up on their own.

00:01:35.409 --> 00:01:36.410
Hello?

00:01:40.080 --> 00:01:42.708
BEOMCHEON-DONG, CAFÉ C'EST…

00:01:43.959 --> 00:01:47.003
Got it. I'll see you tomorrow. Bye.

00:01:51.133 --> 00:01:53.552
They said they'll pay double.

00:01:54.052 --> 00:01:56.221
Let's just give it
and send them away. Go get it.

00:01:59.891 --> 00:02:01.101
Hurry, go grab it.

00:02:29.421 --> 00:02:31.715
What? Have you lost your mind?

00:02:31.798 --> 00:02:34.509
What the hell are you doing?

00:04:24.911 --> 00:04:26.913
Huh? Mr. Jang.

00:04:27.998 --> 00:04:28.999
Be careful.

00:04:46.850 --> 00:04:49.269
Evening, sir.

00:04:52.314 --> 00:04:53.690
The victims were married.

00:04:53.773 --> 00:04:57.527
Kim Taeyeong, 29 years old,
and his wife, Lee Suni, 26.

00:04:58.069 --> 00:05:00.155
They had a three-year-old daughter, and…

00:05:02.699 --> 00:05:04.242
the wife was pregnant.

00:05:05.911 --> 00:05:07.329
Oh, and this.

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:21.760
The US Army already took them
into custody and got their confessions.

00:05:23.803 --> 00:05:24.930
First,

00:05:26.598 --> 00:05:28.058
let's get the kid out of here.

00:05:29.225 --> 00:05:31.269
She doesn't really have
anywhere else to go.

00:05:32.687 --> 00:05:34.773
Her uncle's on his way now.

00:05:37.025 --> 00:05:39.069
Is it because of the rain?

00:05:39.152 --> 00:05:41.529
The whole place reeks of blood.

00:06:00.131 --> 00:06:03.343
BEOMCHEON-DONG,
CAFÉ C'EST LA VIE, 6 P.M., 1 KG

00:06:07.847 --> 00:06:09.891
This child's parents were drug dealers.

00:06:10.976 --> 00:06:16.314
Middlemen who got meth from suppliers
and sold it on to end consumers.

00:06:18.066 --> 00:06:20.068
The couple seemed as ordinary as anyone,

00:06:20.652 --> 00:06:23.571
but they were murdered
by US soldiers while dealing drugs.

00:06:26.533 --> 00:06:29.119
Those US soldiers were addicted to meth.

00:06:30.412 --> 00:06:32.956
They never had the money
to buy it in the first place.

00:06:34.124 --> 00:06:35.959
With no money, they had to steal.

00:06:37.085 --> 00:06:38.461
Once you're hooked on meth…

00:06:38.545 --> 00:06:40.213
-Move, please!
-…nothing else matters.

00:06:40.296 --> 00:06:41.339
This way, sir.

00:06:42.007 --> 00:06:44.926
I bet that's what happened
when they killed this girl's parents.

00:06:46.094 --> 00:06:50.598
They decided their own craving
mattered more than someone else's life.

00:06:53.935 --> 00:06:56.312
This girl's name is Kim Huijeong.

00:06:57.522 --> 00:06:59.315
Now that her parents are dead,

00:06:59.816 --> 00:07:02.986
the bottle in her mouth
is all she has to survive on.

00:07:04.279 --> 00:07:06.865
When she grows up,
will she remember this moment?

00:07:08.450 --> 00:07:10.618
People say time heals all wounds.

00:07:11.619 --> 00:07:13.955
That everything gets better with time.

00:07:15.415 --> 00:07:18.251
But this girl will remember this
for the rest of her life.

00:07:19.836 --> 00:07:22.088
Her own face as she sucked on the bottle,

00:07:23.047 --> 00:07:25.925
her parents' faces as their throats
were cut over a drug deal,

00:07:26.676 --> 00:07:28.845
and the stench of blood
that filled the room.

00:07:31.473 --> 00:07:33.224
If there really is a God,

00:07:34.642 --> 00:07:36.060
may he save this girl's soul

00:07:37.353 --> 00:07:39.731
from the power of the dog.

00:08:46.256 --> 00:08:47.507
Ah, ah.

00:09:04.107 --> 00:09:06.025
Good afternoon, sir.

00:09:06.109 --> 00:09:07.110
What's that?

00:09:07.193 --> 00:09:10.029
Well, I went home
to grab some files I'd forgotten.

00:09:10.113 --> 00:09:11.781
- On your bike?
- Yes.

00:09:12.907 --> 00:09:14.450
Did you guys eat yet?

00:09:14.534 --> 00:09:15.535
Yes.

00:09:15.618 --> 00:09:17.036
Sure did.

00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:19.497
Can you order me
a jjajangmyeon? Make it extra-large.

00:09:19.581 --> 00:09:22.834
- Yes, sir.
- Hey, Jang!

00:09:24.377 --> 00:09:25.503
Listen.

00:09:26.171 --> 00:09:28.381
You said you weren't
taking public security cases.

00:09:30.049 --> 00:09:31.176
That's right.

00:09:31.259 --> 00:09:33.761
Then focus on narcotics.

00:09:34.804 --> 00:09:37.056
Why are you poking around
in a public security case?

00:09:37.140 --> 00:09:41.769
It's connected to the victims
in my case, so I looked into it.

00:09:42.979 --> 00:09:46.107
Being a KCIA informant doesn't mean
you can't be a junkie too, right?

00:09:46.191 --> 00:09:47.192
Jang.

00:09:47.859 --> 00:09:49.903
When I first met you at the Seoul Office,

00:09:49.986 --> 00:09:53.448
I was a section chief, and you were
just a prosecutor with no title, right?

00:09:53.531 --> 00:09:56.242
And when I was in Gwangju
as a departmental chief,

00:09:57.118 --> 00:09:58.578
you still had no title.

00:09:58.661 --> 00:10:02.540
And now, I've been sent here
to Busan as the deputy chief prosecutor.

00:10:02.624 --> 00:10:05.835
But you? You're still without a title.

00:10:06.419 --> 00:10:10.048
All your peers are section chiefs now,
some moving up to departmental chiefs.

00:10:10.131 --> 00:10:14.344
How long will you keep drifting
around the country without a title?

00:10:15.178 --> 00:10:19.182
Well, all I can do is give it my best.

00:10:19.265 --> 00:10:22.227
That's exactly why
you never get promoted. You're too rigid.

00:10:22.310 --> 00:10:24.103
No flexibility!

00:10:24.812 --> 00:10:27.774
Learn to work the hierarchy.

00:10:27.857 --> 00:10:30.360
What do you think an organization is, huh?

00:10:31.945 --> 00:10:35.365
An organization is a place where you work.

00:10:35.448 --> 00:10:38.284
I still have work to do,
so I'd better get to it now.

00:10:39.369 --> 00:10:41.496
Jang. Don't mess with the KCIA, all right?

00:10:41.579 --> 00:10:44.499
Cross them and we're
the only ones who bleed.

00:10:44.582 --> 00:10:48.211
Okay. I'll keep that
in mind and do my best, sir.

00:10:48.795 --> 00:10:51.464
We certainly can't have
bloodshed on the job.

00:10:51.547 --> 00:10:53.007
You're impossible.

00:10:53.675 --> 00:10:56.052
Open a window in here, will you?
It smells like…

00:10:57.262 --> 00:10:59.681
And turn the lights on!
It's so dark in here.

00:10:59.764 --> 00:11:01.474
-Yes, sir.
-What is this, a rat's nest?

00:11:01.557 --> 00:11:03.017
Geez.

00:11:03.601 --> 00:11:04.644
Well, I'm off!

00:11:05.395 --> 00:11:07.855
Good day, sir!

00:11:08.898 --> 00:11:10.441
Turn them off.

00:11:11.484 --> 00:11:12.485
The lights.

00:11:14.737 --> 00:11:16.155
Goodness.

00:11:18.574 --> 00:11:20.785
It's nice and gloomy, isn't it?

00:11:26.791 --> 00:11:29.627
- You order my jjajangmyeon yet?
- Yes, sir.

00:11:35.216 --> 00:11:38.011
DIRECTOR GENERAL HWANG GUKPYEONG

00:11:39.762 --> 00:11:42.265
Director General Hwang Gukpyeong,
my direct superior.

00:11:42.765 --> 00:11:44.892
In charge of the entire
Busan branch of the KCIA.

00:11:44.976 --> 00:11:45.977
It got on me.

00:11:46.060 --> 00:11:48.104
One word from him,
and the whole city moves.

00:11:48.187 --> 00:11:50.773
Anyway,

00:11:52.692 --> 00:11:53.985
about Jo Manjae.

00:11:56.321 --> 00:11:59.073
I hear he's been
dealing meth with the Yakuza.

00:11:59.157 --> 00:12:00.158
Yes, I'm aware.

00:12:05.872 --> 00:12:07.081
You're aware?

00:12:08.166 --> 00:12:09.167
Yes, sir.

00:12:15.840 --> 00:12:19.093
That meth is what I loaded
onto the plane and sent off to Pyongyang.

00:12:19.177 --> 00:12:20.345
The Manjae Gang's meth.

00:12:43.493 --> 00:12:46.162
The Manjae Gang,
Busan's biggest crime syndicate.

00:12:47.330 --> 00:12:49.165
KANG DAEIL,
THE MANJAE GANG UNDERBOSS

00:12:49.248 --> 00:12:51.000
JO MANJAE,
THE MANJAE GANG BOSS

00:12:51.084 --> 00:12:54.670
Under Director Hwang's protection,
they grew fast.

00:12:54.754 --> 00:12:58.091
They kick back 30%
of their monthly take to him,

00:12:58.174 --> 00:13:00.301
straight into the KCIA's pocket.

00:13:02.303 --> 00:13:04.555
The gang pulls every crime in the book

00:13:04.639 --> 00:13:06.849
and rakes in a million dollars
from the underworld.

00:13:06.933 --> 00:13:10.186
At this point, you could say
they practically run the Busan economy.

00:13:20.947 --> 00:13:24.951
THE POWER OF THE DOG

00:13:25.535 --> 00:13:28.996
I was planning to take care of it myself.

00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:32.291
Jang Geonyoung, a prosecutor
at the Busan District Prosecutors' Office,

00:13:32.375 --> 00:13:35.545
is apparently gunning for Jo Manjae,
all fired up.

00:13:35.628 --> 00:13:38.881
They say he's a Marine legend
who once took down armed guerrillas

00:13:38.965 --> 00:13:42.844
with his bare hands and got
a Hwarang Order of Military Merit for it.

00:13:42.927 --> 00:13:48.641
And he's the kind of loose cannon
who doesn't give a damn about higher-ups.

00:13:49.809 --> 00:13:52.562
So how do you plan on
handling him, Mr. Baek?

00:13:53.938 --> 00:13:55.356
Don't worry, sir.

00:13:55.439 --> 00:13:57.400
I'll take care of him myself.

00:14:18.796 --> 00:14:21.007
Why don't you guys go out for a smoke?

00:14:23.509 --> 00:14:25.011
Sit.

00:14:28.598 --> 00:14:31.058
- Everything good while I was away?
- Yes, sir. All good.

00:14:32.560 --> 00:14:35.104
Listen, look into
Prosecutor Jang Geonyoung

00:14:35.188 --> 00:14:37.648
at the Busan District Prosecutors' Office.

00:14:37.732 --> 00:14:40.985
His background, family,
relatives, friends, personality…

00:14:41.068 --> 00:14:44.238
Well, whatever it is,
don't miss a single detail.

00:14:44.864 --> 00:14:47.575
Dig up every last thing
connected to him and bring it to me.

00:14:48.075 --> 00:14:49.076
Yes, sir.

00:14:58.127 --> 00:15:01.130
Ah. Nice to meet you. John Evans.

00:15:01.214 --> 00:15:02.298
Just call me John.

00:15:03.299 --> 00:15:04.634
Okay, John.

00:15:06.219 --> 00:15:08.429
What are those bastards doing here?

00:15:09.013 --> 00:15:10.806
Exercise. One hour per day.

00:15:11.974 --> 00:15:15.144
The murderers have rights too? Hmm?

00:15:15.228 --> 00:15:16.520
Don't they in Korea?

00:15:21.567 --> 00:15:23.110
Let's get done with this quickly.

00:15:23.194 --> 00:15:26.697
We've already provided enough information
with the police regarding their cases.

00:15:27.740 --> 00:15:29.116
That's different, man.

00:15:30.326 --> 00:15:31.327
Look.

00:15:31.994 --> 00:15:32.995
Hmm?

00:15:34.830 --> 00:15:36.999
In the corner. Here.

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:38.834
Something's written.

00:15:39.627 --> 00:15:41.712
Remember the man you killed?

00:15:41.796 --> 00:15:45.967
He wrote it down when he was in the phone…

00:15:46.050 --> 00:15:47.301
No. On the phone.

00:15:48.135 --> 00:15:49.136
Hmm?

00:15:49.637 --> 00:15:52.723
Any phone call when you were in the house?

00:15:54.976 --> 00:15:58.062
Uh… Mr. Kim picked up the phone
and wrote something down on the paper.

00:15:58.562 --> 00:15:59.563
Okay.

00:16:01.607 --> 00:16:02.608
But…

00:16:03.734 --> 00:16:04.777
if you look at it,

00:16:05.361 --> 00:16:06.779
there's no date.

00:16:07.863 --> 00:16:10.783
Only the time and place.

00:16:10.866 --> 00:16:13.202
It's a deal. A drug deal.

00:16:13.828 --> 00:16:15.788
Is there anything you heard about it?

00:16:15.871 --> 00:16:17.498
These guys cannot understand Korean.

00:16:17.581 --> 00:16:20.418
Even if they heard something,
they wouldn't know what it meant.

00:16:23.087 --> 00:16:26.257
Yeah, I know.
But I wanted to ask, just in case.

00:16:26.340 --> 00:16:29.635
They should know a few words in Korean,
now that they're in Korea.

00:16:29.719 --> 00:16:31.929
- So damn disrespectful.
- What?

00:16:33.389 --> 00:16:34.432
Okay.

00:16:34.515 --> 00:16:38.853
Now, you listen carefully. Hmm?

00:16:38.936 --> 00:16:40.229
To what I say.

00:16:44.567 --> 00:16:46.027
"If you cooperate with me,

00:16:46.110 --> 00:16:49.155
I may be able to cut down your sentence.

00:16:49.238 --> 00:16:53.326
Then you can be sent back
to your country in a few years,

00:16:53.409 --> 00:16:58.372
or I could even let you serve
your sentence in the States."

00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:00.041
Understand?

00:17:00.541 --> 00:17:01.542
It's a deal!

00:17:02.084 --> 00:17:03.544
It's a deal!

00:17:03.627 --> 00:17:05.254
"See you tomorrow."

00:17:10.301 --> 00:17:13.346
Mr. Kim said, "See you tomorrow."

00:17:13.929 --> 00:17:14.930
You speak Korean?

00:17:15.014 --> 00:17:16.432
My girlfriend's Korean.

00:17:20.061 --> 00:17:21.145
Tomorrow?

00:17:21.729 --> 00:17:22.730
You sure?

00:17:23.773 --> 00:17:26.275
- Tomorrow.
- I'm sure.

00:17:27.360 --> 00:17:28.361
Good job.

00:17:32.073 --> 00:17:33.074
Oh, right.

00:17:34.283 --> 00:17:35.368
By the way…

00:17:36.952 --> 00:17:39.288
The woman you killed, Lee Suni.

00:17:42.458 --> 00:17:44.669
She was pregnant.

00:17:54.762 --> 00:17:56.389
We've received intel

00:17:56.472 --> 00:17:58.557
that the meth dealers murdered last night,

00:17:58.641 --> 00:18:01.519
Kim Taeyeong and his wife, Lee Suni,

00:18:01.602 --> 00:18:07.191
had a deal lined up
with their supplier today at 6:00 p.m.

00:18:07.274 --> 00:18:10.319
at the Café C'est La Vie
in Beomcheon-dong.

00:18:10.403 --> 00:18:15.574
Assuming the supplier doesn't know
they're dead yet, he's expected to show.

00:18:15.658 --> 00:18:18.828
Two of our investigators
will pose as the couple on site

00:18:18.911 --> 00:18:21.455
and the moment he shows up,
we move in for the arrest.

00:18:24.750 --> 00:18:26.043
Hello, I'm here.

00:18:26.669 --> 00:18:28.212
Ah, Ms. Oh!

00:18:28.295 --> 00:18:31.465
Sir, this is Ms. Oh.
She'll be playing the wife.

00:18:34.093 --> 00:18:35.511
Hello, sir.

00:18:36.137 --> 00:18:38.973
I'm Oh Yejin.
I've just been assigned to the team.

00:18:39.056 --> 00:18:41.517
I'll be playing the wife, Lee Suni,
in today's operation.

00:18:41.600 --> 00:18:43.728
Right. Welcome aboard, Investigator Oh.

00:18:45.187 --> 00:18:47.857
So… What about the husband?

00:18:47.940 --> 00:18:48.941
Right.

00:18:51.861 --> 00:18:52.862
That's me.

00:18:56.866 --> 00:18:58.826
We'll need to find you
a different husband.

00:18:58.909 --> 00:19:00.453
I think that's a good idea, sir.

00:19:00.536 --> 00:19:02.246
Wait, why? What's wrong?

00:19:04.790 --> 00:19:05.958
Attention, everyone!

00:19:08.002 --> 00:19:09.253
All right,

00:19:10.212 --> 00:19:11.839
choose your husband from among them.

00:19:12.923 --> 00:19:14.425
You think they're any better?

00:19:24.477 --> 00:19:25.519
What?

00:19:37.072 --> 00:19:38.783
MUSIC CAFÉ C'EST LA VIE
COFFEE &amp; TEA

00:19:38.866 --> 00:19:40.117
Welcome.

00:19:53.172 --> 00:19:54.799
C'est La Vie.

00:19:57.343 --> 00:19:58.469
Mr. Kim Taeyeong?

00:20:05.726 --> 00:20:06.727
Hello?

00:20:07.228 --> 00:20:10.272
Take Bus 57 and get off
at Myeonhak-ri Station.

00:20:16.695 --> 00:20:19.198
Wait, too fast. Hey, slow down.

00:20:19.281 --> 00:20:20.616
Slow down. Come on.

00:20:24.578 --> 00:20:26.664
They're not going to lose us, right?

00:20:30.209 --> 00:20:32.253
Just act natural.

00:20:32.336 --> 00:20:33.671
Don't be so nervous.

00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:35.881
Right.

00:20:38.801 --> 00:20:39.927
Hmm.

00:20:40.010 --> 00:20:41.011
Okay then.

00:20:41.929 --> 00:20:44.014
Mind if I ask you something?

00:20:44.098 --> 00:20:45.182
Sure, what is it?

00:20:46.392 --> 00:20:47.393
Well…

00:20:50.020 --> 00:20:53.566
Have you always been
this good-looking, Mr. Jang?

00:20:58.153 --> 00:20:59.154
Are you…

00:21:01.740 --> 00:21:04.076
hitting on me just to loosen up?

00:21:05.619 --> 00:21:07.288
Come on, of course not.

00:21:07.371 --> 00:21:09.832
Someone like me hitting on you? No way.

00:21:10.499 --> 00:21:12.459
You think I'd make a fool of myself,

00:21:12.543 --> 00:21:15.379
hitting on someone who's not interested?

00:21:16.839 --> 00:21:18.257
I must be losing my mind.

00:21:18.340 --> 00:21:20.217
My nerves have me speaking nonsense.

00:21:21.802 --> 00:21:24.513
But I really did want to ask you that.

00:21:26.390 --> 00:21:28.017
Just forget it. I'm sorry.

00:21:33.939 --> 00:21:36.901
I hear you studied law at PNU
and took the bar exam.

00:21:36.984 --> 00:21:37.985
Ah…

00:21:38.777 --> 00:21:39.987
Yes, that's right.

00:21:40.070 --> 00:21:41.697
Will you try again this year?

00:21:45.075 --> 00:21:46.076
Well, that's…

00:21:47.036 --> 00:21:48.037
Are you giving up?

00:21:49.830 --> 00:21:51.373
Even if I pass, what's the point?

00:21:51.457 --> 00:21:53.417
