00:41:53.282 --> 00:41:54.909
Sounds good to me.

00:41:56.869 --> 00:41:58.246
Wait for me!

00:41:58.913 --> 00:42:00.164
How about jjajangmyeon?

00:42:08.965 --> 00:42:10.049
No answer.

00:42:22.478 --> 00:42:25.481
PROSECUTION SERVICE

00:42:34.031 --> 00:42:36.033
BUSAN DISTRICT
PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

00:43:42.016 --> 00:43:43.851
PERSONAL RECORD
NAME: KANG DAEIL

00:43:43.935 --> 00:43:46.062
PERSONAL RECORD
NAME: JO MANJAE

00:43:46.979 --> 00:43:48.731
Look at all this crap.

00:44:08.751 --> 00:44:10.670
PORT OF BUSAN METH SMUGGLING

00:44:20.096 --> 00:44:22.223
THE MANJAE GANG

00:44:52.420 --> 00:44:53.421
Hey, Jang.

00:44:54.130 --> 00:44:55.172
Join me for lunch.

00:44:56.007 --> 00:44:58.301
I'm meeting with the chief editor
of Joguk Ilbo.

00:44:58.384 --> 00:45:01.595
-You haven't eaten yet, have you?
-Oh, dear. I just ate, actually.

00:45:02.346 --> 00:45:04.265
Yeah? Then drop by my office later.

00:45:04.348 --> 00:45:06.600
- I've got something to tell you.
- Yes, sir.

00:45:06.684 --> 00:45:09.520
Right. I'll be tied up
questioning suspects this afternoon.

00:45:09.603 --> 00:45:10.730
I'll come by tomorrow morning.

00:45:10.813 --> 00:45:12.148
- All right.
- Yeah.

00:45:12.231 --> 00:45:15.151
Hey, Jang! You'd better show up!

00:45:16.986 --> 00:45:17.987
Let's clear out.

00:46:12.958 --> 00:46:17.838
Looks like everyone thoughtlessly
ran off to lunch once again,

00:46:17.922 --> 00:46:20.800
with papers lying around
and the door unlocked.

00:46:21.967 --> 00:46:23.135
And you are?

00:46:28.224 --> 00:46:31.685
I'm Baek Kitae, KCIA Busan branch.

00:46:31.769 --> 00:46:33.813
This guy's name

00:46:33.896 --> 00:46:35.523
is Baek Kitae.

00:46:35.606 --> 00:46:37.316
That guy next to Jo Manjae.

00:46:39.568 --> 00:46:41.028
He's with the KCIA?

00:46:42.029 --> 00:46:44.281
Jang Geonyoung,
Busan District Prosecutors' Office.

00:46:47.827 --> 00:46:50.621
So, what brings the KCIA all the way here?

00:46:50.704 --> 00:46:52.623
There must be a reason

00:46:52.706 --> 00:46:56.627
you're standing in the middle of
someone else's office while they're out.

00:46:58.462 --> 00:46:59.630
You know Jo Manjae, right?

00:47:00.589 --> 00:47:02.091
The Manjae Gang's number one.

00:47:02.174 --> 00:47:03.217
Right, the Manjae Gang.

00:47:04.218 --> 00:47:05.219
I came here

00:47:06.554 --> 00:47:09.390
to ask you to drop Jo Manjae. Lay off him.

00:47:14.937 --> 00:47:18.065
You're telling me
to shut down my investigation?

00:47:18.732 --> 00:47:19.984
The KCIA

00:47:21.318 --> 00:47:22.862
giving orders to a prosecutor?

00:47:25.865 --> 00:47:27.741
I didn't mean it like that.

00:47:29.785 --> 00:47:30.995
Then what?

00:47:31.579 --> 00:47:33.289
At least give me a proper explanation.

00:47:37.543 --> 00:47:41.338
Did you know Jo Manjae's
married to a Zainichi?

00:47:41.422 --> 00:47:42.465
Yes.

00:47:46.093 --> 00:47:47.928
According to our recent intel,

00:47:48.637 --> 00:47:51.557
his wife has been deeply involved
with North Korea.

00:47:55.060 --> 00:47:56.729
Ah.

00:47:58.063 --> 00:48:00.524
So Jo Manjae is tangled up
with commies now, huh?

00:48:00.608 --> 00:48:04.153
We got word that his gang's been
pushing meth up North through Japan.

00:48:04.236 --> 00:48:06.947
We've been running an operation
on this for over a year now.

00:48:07.907 --> 00:48:10.701
I went undercover
to make contact with Jo Manjae myself.

00:48:10.784 --> 00:48:14.079
So you're saying,
the KCIA's already working him,

00:48:15.080 --> 00:48:16.332
and I'm supposed to back off?

00:48:16.415 --> 00:48:18.292
We're all civil servants here.

00:48:18.375 --> 00:48:20.252
We should help one another, shouldn't we?

00:48:20.794 --> 00:48:22.630
It's all for the country after all.

00:48:31.180 --> 00:48:32.389
Okay!

00:48:32.473 --> 00:48:33.849
Got it.

00:48:34.808 --> 00:48:36.477
I'll leave Jo Manjae to you then.

00:48:37.186 --> 00:48:38.938
That goddamn commie.

00:48:39.021 --> 00:48:41.524
Thank you for understanding.

00:48:41.607 --> 00:48:43.275
Gosh, don't mention it.

00:48:43.817 --> 00:48:46.070
You moved to Busan
about two months ago, right?

00:48:46.153 --> 00:48:47.321
Yeah, that's right.

00:48:47.905 --> 00:48:51.075
You're from Seoul, so I bet
it hasn't been easy settling in here.

00:48:51.867 --> 00:48:53.994
We should grab some raw fish sometime.

00:48:54.078 --> 00:48:55.871
I'll take you someplace nice.

00:48:55.955 --> 00:48:58.165
Ah, actually…

00:49:00.209 --> 00:49:02.002
I'm not really into raw fish.

00:49:02.836 --> 00:49:04.421
When we get the chance,

00:49:04.505 --> 00:49:07.216
let's have some soju instead,
with pork and rice soup.

00:49:07.299 --> 00:49:08.300
That sounds good too.

00:49:08.842 --> 00:49:10.636
All right, then. I'll give you a call.

00:49:28.195 --> 00:49:30.322
Jo Manjae is…

00:49:32.700 --> 00:49:34.785
tied up with commies, huh?

00:49:46.422 --> 00:49:47.798
Yeah, right.

00:49:48.340 --> 00:49:50.759
Who the hell does he think he's fooling?

00:50:14.450 --> 00:50:16.076
- Let's go eat.
- Yes, sir.

00:50:27.421 --> 00:50:29.923
Mr. Jang isn't here yet.

00:50:34.136 --> 00:50:36.430
- Turn the lights off.
- Damn, you scared me.

00:50:37.014 --> 00:50:38.724
It's broad daylight.

00:50:38.807 --> 00:50:40.017
I didn't see you there.

00:50:41.268 --> 00:50:42.978
Save if you want a better life.

00:50:43.562 --> 00:50:47.399
Well, I picked up some lunch for you.

00:50:47.983 --> 00:50:49.026
Have you eaten yet?

00:50:49.693 --> 00:50:50.694
No.

00:50:51.362 --> 00:50:52.738
Where's Mr. Kim and…

00:50:52.821 --> 00:50:54.073
Where is everyone?

00:50:54.156 --> 00:50:55.824
He said he was going to court.

00:50:55.908 --> 00:50:58.035
The other investigators
are out at the scene.

00:51:10.130 --> 00:51:11.924
Were you hungry?

00:51:12.007 --> 00:51:14.176
Slow down, or you'll get indigestion.

00:51:14.259 --> 00:51:17.096
Here. Take a look.

00:51:20.557 --> 00:51:21.850
What's this?

00:51:23.268 --> 00:51:24.853
9TH, 8 P.M.
ROOM 611, BUSAN HOTEL

00:51:24.937 --> 00:51:26.897
He says the Yakuza's coming to Busan.

00:51:28.482 --> 00:51:29.525
The Yakuza?

00:51:29.608 --> 00:51:30.609
Yes.

00:51:32.027 --> 00:51:35.406
He's meeting Jo Manjae at Busan Hotel.

00:51:35.489 --> 00:51:38.033
Uh… It's about the meth, right?

00:51:39.159 --> 00:51:40.411
That's what it looks like.

00:51:41.036 --> 00:51:42.037
Damn.

00:51:43.539 --> 00:51:44.915
This time…

00:51:47.084 --> 00:51:49.169
we have to get Jo Manjae.

00:51:51.463 --> 00:51:52.464
Hang on.

00:51:53.173 --> 00:51:54.174
The 9th?

00:51:54.675 --> 00:51:56.552
That's the day after tomorrow, isn't it?

00:51:56.635 --> 00:51:58.637
That's right.
The day after tomorrow.

00:51:59.555 --> 00:52:02.391
Oh, right. The KCIA was here earlier.

00:52:05.269 --> 00:52:07.604
- The KCIA? W-Why?
- Yeah.

00:52:08.188 --> 00:52:09.189
What business…

00:52:10.899 --> 00:52:12.025
could they possibly have

00:52:12.776 --> 00:52:14.862
here at the Busan District
Prosecutors' Office?

00:52:14.945 --> 00:52:16.238
What could've brought the KCIA here?

00:52:16.321 --> 00:52:19.241
Exactly.
What could've brought them here?

00:52:19.324 --> 00:52:20.409
Look at this guy.

00:53:22.012 --> 00:53:23.138
Boss, he's here.

00:53:23.680 --> 00:53:24.807
Yeah? All right.

00:53:28.977 --> 00:53:31.814
Pleasure to meet you. I'm Jo Manjae.

00:53:37.069 --> 00:53:38.237
He says hello.

00:53:38.987 --> 00:53:40.864
Have a seat.

00:53:47.663 --> 00:53:51.291
So, is this your first time in Busan?

00:53:59.007 --> 00:54:00.843
He used to live here as a kid.

00:54:02.052 --> 00:54:04.721
So he's a Zainichi?

00:54:12.187 --> 00:54:15.607
He's Japanese, and he was here in 1944.

00:54:17.651 --> 00:54:19.027
That's before liberation.

00:54:20.404 --> 00:54:25.951
My grandfather was killed by a Jap bullet
at the Battle of Cheongsan-ri, you know.

00:54:26.034 --> 00:54:28.620
Uh…

00:54:28.704 --> 00:54:29.705
Well…

00:54:35.836 --> 00:54:37.045
Well, never mind.

00:54:38.213 --> 00:54:41.967
History's history,
and business is business, eh?

00:54:44.595 --> 00:54:46.096
Go get the stuff.

00:54:46.597 --> 00:54:48.932
Uh… We'll bring it to you now.

00:54:56.648 --> 00:54:57.816
Looks good.

00:54:58.942 --> 00:55:00.319
But…

00:55:01.862 --> 00:55:04.031
you think you can move
10 kilos every month?

00:55:05.324 --> 00:55:07.618
He's asking if we can do
10 kilos every month.

00:55:08.368 --> 00:55:09.786
Let's see the cash first.

00:55:14.791 --> 00:55:15.792
Hey.

00:55:23.008 --> 00:55:25.052
Tell him we can do 20 kilos.

00:55:29.556 --> 00:55:31.058
That's impressive.

00:55:32.517 --> 00:55:33.518
"Sugoi"?

00:55:34.478 --> 00:55:36.104
"Sugoi" means "impressive."

00:55:39.399 --> 00:55:40.567
Cheers.

00:55:44.196 --> 00:55:46.490
Sounds like they're hitting it off, huh?

00:55:48.033 --> 00:55:49.242
All right.

00:55:49.826 --> 00:55:51.828
I'd say we're good to go.

00:56:01.338 --> 00:56:02.547
We got it on tape, right?

00:56:06.218 --> 00:56:07.219
All right.

00:56:07.302 --> 00:56:10.013
Everyone, grab your gear. Let's go.

00:56:14.518 --> 00:56:15.519
Move in.

00:56:22.567 --> 00:56:24.778
Turn the light on. The light.

00:56:24.861 --> 00:56:27.614
I think it's a blackout. What do we do?

00:56:34.204 --> 00:56:36.456
- Hey, go see what's going on.
- Yes, sir.

00:56:41.712 --> 00:56:43.213
What the hell?

00:56:45.632 --> 00:56:47.384
Stop resisting, you bastards!

00:56:47.467 --> 00:56:49.970
- On your knees, punk!
- On your knees!

00:56:52.264 --> 00:56:53.557
Open the door!

00:56:55.100 --> 00:56:56.184
Hey, you bastard!

00:57:01.106 --> 00:57:02.649
Open the fucking door!

00:57:14.369 --> 00:57:15.787
All clear, sir.

00:57:29.760 --> 00:57:32.763
Open the door! Hey, open the door!

00:57:47.235 --> 00:57:48.737
Get the tear gas!

00:57:50.614 --> 00:57:51.948
Head on the ground, asshole!

00:57:52.532 --> 00:57:53.533
Hey!

00:58:15.138 --> 00:58:16.640
Hey, the tear gas!

00:58:18.099 --> 00:58:19.810
Shit, it's hot!

00:58:19.893 --> 00:58:21.186
It's hot!

00:58:24.272 --> 00:58:25.774
Move!

00:58:27.150 --> 00:58:28.568
Move!

00:58:28.652 --> 00:58:30.195
Move!

00:59:09.860 --> 00:59:11.945
Do you not realize how serious this is?

00:59:12.863 --> 00:59:14.865
The Japanese Metropolitan
Police Department

00:59:14.948 --> 00:59:17.200
put those Yakuza bastards
on the wanted list.

00:59:17.868 --> 00:59:20.620
They even sent over a formal request
for cooperation, Mr. Jo.

00:59:20.704 --> 00:59:24.291
Sir, I'm really sorry
we didn't clear it with you first.

00:59:24.958 --> 00:59:27.794
But still, after everything
we've paid up until now,

00:59:27.878 --> 00:59:29.921
isn't this the time
you step in and cover us?

00:59:30.005 --> 00:59:31.256
Who the hell is this guy?

00:59:33.049 --> 00:59:35.385
Sir, please forgive him.

00:59:35.468 --> 00:59:38.388
This guy doesn't…
He doesn't know any better.

00:59:38.471 --> 00:59:39.890
It won't happen again.

00:59:40.390 --> 00:59:42.684
We just got a little greedy and messed up.

00:59:42.767 --> 00:59:47.397
If you help us out just this once,
we'll make sure to pay you back for it!

00:59:47.480 --> 00:59:50.692
Wow. This one's got
more guts than him, right?

00:59:50.775 --> 00:59:51.943
Hey, you're better.

00:59:52.485 --> 00:59:54.529
Yeah, you're right.

00:59:55.030 --> 00:59:57.407
He's got guts.
If you'd forgive us just this once…

01:00:05.081 --> 01:00:07.584
Shut it.

01:00:17.469 --> 01:00:20.263
Sir, it's probably best to leave him.

01:00:21.056 --> 01:00:24.768
We'll need someone to pull the gang
back together as their new leader.

01:00:29.481 --> 01:00:31.274
The election's right around the corner.

01:00:41.076 --> 01:00:42.285
You think you can do well?

01:00:44.829 --> 01:00:45.830
Yes, sir.

01:00:46.373 --> 01:00:47.374
Yeah?

01:00:59.928 --> 01:01:01.471
On your knees!

01:01:01.554 --> 01:01:04.265
- Stay still!
- Stop resisting!

01:01:05.600 --> 01:01:07.060
On your knees!

01:01:07.143 --> 01:01:09.854
- Stay still!
- Stop resisting!

01:01:11.189 --> 01:01:12.190
On your knees!

01:01:12.273 --> 01:01:14.818
- Stay still!
- Stop resisting!

01:01:19.030 --> 01:01:22.242
Who the hell screwed us over
and snatched Jo Manjae?

01:01:23.410 --> 01:01:25.620
- Hello. So…
- Morning, sir.

01:01:25.704 --> 01:01:29.457
Did you guys clean the office yet?

01:01:30.875 --> 01:01:32.502
- Clean?
- No, we didn't…

01:01:32.585 --> 01:01:34.629
How many times
have I told you to clean up?

01:01:34.713 --> 01:01:36.214
Just look at this place!

01:01:36.297 --> 01:01:37.632
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Huh?

01:01:37.716 --> 01:01:41.136
Ms. Oh, go and…
Go get the broom and the dustpan.

01:01:41.219 --> 01:01:43.138
Yes, sir.
I'll bring the dustpan and sweep up.

01:01:43.221 --> 01:01:46.641
And these useless boxes.
Get them all out to the storage room!

01:01:46.725 --> 01:01:48.018
Okay, I'll clear them out.

01:01:48.101 --> 01:01:50.228
And what the hell
is this bag doing here, huh?

01:01:50.311 --> 01:01:52.313
Why would you leave
a bag lying around here?

01:01:52.397 --> 01:01:53.982
- I'm sorry.
- I'll put it away.

01:02:05.535 --> 01:02:06.911
Lay low for a while.

01:02:09.080 --> 01:02:10.665
You don't have to give me all this.

01:02:12.250 --> 01:02:14.210
I won't breathe a word to Director Hwang.

01:02:14.294 --> 01:02:15.628
Don't worry, sir.

01:02:17.422 --> 01:02:19.466
If I was worried
about you running your mouth,

01:02:19.549 --> 01:02:21.092
I would've let you die back there.

01:02:21.926 --> 01:02:23.178
Then why did you…

01:02:23.261 --> 01:02:24.262
I told you.

01:02:25.472 --> 01:02:27.766
You're Jo Manjae's replacement now.

01:02:27.849 --> 01:02:29.934
The whole gang's already in pieces,

01:02:31.061 --> 01:02:33.104
so why would you even need a replacement?

01:02:34.689 --> 01:02:35.690
The business.

01:02:36.566 --> 01:02:38.318
You've got to keep it going, don't you?

01:02:38.818 --> 01:02:42.322
All right, open up the cabinet
and toss out all those old files!

01:02:42.405 --> 01:02:43.406
Yes, sir. I will.

01:02:43.490 --> 01:02:45.617
How many times
have I told you to clean that out?

01:02:45.700 --> 01:02:47.202
I'm sorry.

01:02:53.374 --> 01:02:55.710
And this box!

01:02:55.794 --> 01:02:57.921
- That's…
- I told you a hundred times

01:02:58.004 --> 01:03:00.173
- to throw it out already! Geez!
- That… I'm sorry!

01:03:00.256 --> 01:03:02.717
Mr. Jang, please
just leave it. We'll take care of it.

01:03:02.801 --> 01:03:04.594
Just leave it. We'll do it.

01:03:09.140 --> 01:03:10.517
Me?

01:03:14.104 --> 01:03:15.105
You.

01:03:16.106 --> 01:03:17.107
Me.

01:03:17.857 --> 01:03:20.110
Us.

01:03:23.863 --> 01:03:25.782
That meth business of yours.

01:03:27.826 --> 01:03:30.036
I've had my eye on it for a long time.

01:03:31.121 --> 01:03:32.705
Mr. Baek, I heard

01:03:33.623 --> 01:03:36.501
you'll be going to Japan soon.

01:03:36.584 --> 01:03:37.961
Would it be all right

01:03:38.503 --> 01:03:40.588
if I asked you a small favor on your way?

01:03:41.506 --> 01:03:45.093
That's why
I did you guys the favor.

01:03:46.886 --> 01:03:50.140
I'll figure out a way to reopen
the connection with the Japanese.

01:03:50.932 --> 01:03:52.016
In the meantime,

01:03:52.767 --> 01:03:54.978
you take that money,
pull the guys back together,

01:03:55.603 --> 01:03:57.730
and get the lab running again.

01:03:58.398 --> 01:04:00.358
You want to sell the drugs yourself?

01:04:02.277 --> 01:04:03.278
But…

01:04:03.945 --> 01:04:05.905
A government man dealing drugs…

01:04:08.074 --> 01:04:09.075
What?

01:04:11.119 --> 01:04:12.120
Is that a problem?

01:04:13.121 --> 01:04:14.122
No, sir.

01:04:14.622 --> 01:04:15.623
Not at all.

01:04:21.546 --> 01:04:23.673
I thought
they were just petty thieves,

01:04:24.174 --> 01:04:27.385
but turns out those bastards
are a lot more audacious than I expected.

01:04:27.468 --> 01:04:30.805
I'm Baek Kitae, KCIA Busan branch.

01:04:30.889 --> 01:04:33.141
Mr. Baek Kitae.

01:04:33.224 --> 01:04:35.310
Looks like we'll be seeing
a lot of each other from now on.

01:04:46.112 --> 01:04:48.114
All right, that's enough cleaning!

01:04:48.198 --> 01:04:49.449
Let's get to work!

01:07:23.811 --> 01:07:25.813
Translated by Yoonjung Song